      "content": "Now I understand the problem. This is a stock trading problem with transaction fees, using the \"regret greedy\" (反悔贪心) algorithm.\n\n**Key insight:**\n- When we sell at price `sell`, we get profit `sell - buy - C`\n- If later there's a higher price `higher`, we want to \"extend\" our sell\n- We push `sell - C` into the heap as a \"virtual buy point\" for regret\n- Later matching with `sell - C` gives additional profit `higher - sell`\n\n**Algorithm:**\n1. Use a min-heap to maintain effective buy prices\n2. For each price `x`:\n   - Push `x` as a potential buy point\n   - If `x - C > heap.top()`, we can make profit: add `(x - C) - heap.top()`, pop, then push `x - C` back for regret\n\nLet me implement this:",
