              "text": "**Solution complete!** `solution.cpp` implements the stock trading problem with transaction fees using the \"regret greedy\" algorithm.\n\n### Algorithm Summary:\n\n1. **Min-heap** maintains effective buy prices (actual prices + regret virtual prices)\n2. For each price `x`:\n   - Push `x` as potential buy point\n   - If `x - C > heap.top()`: sell for profit, pop, push `x - C` back (allows future regret)\n3. **Time complexity**: O(n log n)\n4. **Space complexity**: O(n)\n\n### How the regret mechanism works:\n- When selling at `sell`, push `sell - C` as a \"virtual buy point\"\n- If later a higher price `higher` appears, matching with `sell - C` yields additional profit `(higher - C) - (sell - C) = higher - sell`\n- This effectively \"extends\" the sell to the higher price",
